ALL: Amen.

01:56.944 --> 01:58.566
Levi, really?

01:58.704 --> 02:00.534
Slow moving. So annoying.

02:00.672 --> 02:02.812
You know why I'm late, Levi?

02:04.469 --> 02:06.333
Because I had a call
from Mr. Thompson. Dad!

02:08.990 --> 02:11.821
I have enough stress,

02:11.959 --> 02:14.686
with you once more
running over his leaves

02:14.824 --> 02:16.653
is the last thing I need.

02:16.791 --> 02:19.691
Dad, I said I'm sorry. That's what
you said the last time, Levi!

02:19.829 --> 02:21.002
I was sorry last time, too.

02:21.141 --> 02:22.901
Don't you mock me, boy!

02:23.039 --> 02:24.834
Marcus, please.

02:27.975 --> 02:29.183
You got something to say?

02:33.463 --> 02:35.465
Dad, truly,

02:35.603 --> 02:37.398
I apologize.
[METAL CLATTERING]

02:37.536 --> 02:39.297
Pick that up! I'm getting it.

02:42.231 --> 02:43.887
MARCUS: You gonna
go in the morning

02:45.165 --> 02:47.063
and you gonna rake
his leaves for him.

02:47.201 --> 02:48.720
But I have practice in
the morning and...

02:48.858 --> 02:50.446
You should've thought
of that before.

02:50.584 --> 02:54.208
You love your neighbor as you love
yourself, Levi. You got that, boy?

02:55.140 --> 02:56.383
Yes, sir. Huh?

02:57.487 --> 02:58.695
Yes, sir.

03:00.663 --> 03:01.905
[CHUCKLES]

03:18.543 --> 03:20.061
STEVE: You were
quiet last night.

03:27.414 --> 03:30.555
A woman cannot survive on
peanut butter spoon alone.

03:30.693 --> 03:32.626
Not much else to survive on.

03:32.764 --> 03:33.903
Out of milk again?

03:34.800 --> 03:36.423
My bad. Milk bad.

03:36.975 --> 03:38.045
Oh.

03:44.845 --> 03:46.571
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

03:51.886 --> 03:53.233
If you can't beat 'em...

04:00.309 --> 04:02.414
Uh, you need to be
dropped off at work?

04:02.932 --> 04:04.830
Um, yeah.

04:04.968 --> 04:06.936
Please do.
I'll be ready in ten.

04:10.629 --> 04:12.562
[DOOR CLOSES]

04:18.534 --> 04:20.260
