04:22.676 --> 04:25.506
Bri! Dad! Dad, you okay?

04:26.645 --> 04:29.441
Dad, it's okay, I'm okay.

04:29.579 --> 04:31.271
Do you need to go back
and get your meds, or...

04:31.409 --> 04:32.927
No! No!

04:33.583 --> 04:34.826
[PANTING]

04:34.964 --> 04:36.897
No, I'm fine.

04:37.035 --> 04:39.555
It's okay.
I'll be fine.

04:41.073 --> 04:42.558
Just go ahead.

04:44.042 --> 04:45.940
[ENGINE STARTS]

04:49.944 --> 04:51.463
[PLAYING PIANO]

04:51.601 --> 04:53.534
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

05:01.231 --> 05:02.750
All good here, Bri? Yeah.

05:02.888 --> 05:04.131
My hand just slipped.

05:04.269 --> 05:06.202
You working on what
we talked about?

05:06.340 --> 05:07.548
It's not that easy.

05:07.686 --> 05:09.170
It's up to you.

05:44.378 --> 05:47.623
LUCIA: <i>♪ Baby don't
want that booty</i>

05:49.797 --> 05:53.318
<i>♪ Girl don't want
that delicious flavor</i>

05:54.630 --> 05:57.357
<i>♪ Drink that love from my...</i>

05:57.495 --> 05:59.393
<i>♪ What, what, what</i>

05:59.531 --> 06:03.432
<i>♪ Booty, booty, booty booty,
booty, booty bootylicious ♪</i>

06:03.570 --> 06:05.019
[LAUGHS]

06:06.227 --> 06:09.092
Girl, don't you
make me have to...

06:09.230 --> 06:11.163
You got a lot of learning to do.

06:11.301 --> 06:14.374
<i>♪ Mmm, mmm, take that,
take that, take that ♪</i>

06:15.167 --> 06:16.790
Mama, please!

06:16.928 --> 06:18.688
Don't please me,
please yourself.

06:18.826 --> 06:20.759
Girl, you're like water
been on too long,

06:20.897 --> 06:22.243
you're 'bout to boil off.

06:22.382 --> 06:23.866
Get up off that table.

06:24.729 --> 06:27.283
<i>♪ Bootylicious ♪</i>

06:30.079 --> 06:31.977
<i>♪ Booty, booty, booty, booty</i>

06:32.115 --> 06:33.634
<i>♪ Take that, take that ♪</i>

06:34.255 --> 06:35.809
[SCREAMS]

06:35.947 --> 06:37.880
Miss me, now you gotta kiss me.

06:38.018 --> 06:39.571
Oh, girl.

06:39.709 --> 06:42.367
You gone be the death of me.

06:42.505 --> 06:44.921
Mother, I asked you
not to hide the remotes.

06:45.059 --> 06:47.337
You know how Marcus
feels about it.

06:47.476 --> 06:50.306
Well, when he get to the
point where he wants 'em,

06:50.444 --> 06:53.033
Marcus know where to
find 'em, now don't he?

06:54.931 --> 06:56.416
All righty.

06:56.899 --> 06:58.590
Uh-huh.

06:58.728 --> 07:01.421
You sure you don't have something
else to do until I finish?

07:01.559 --> 07:03.112
I mean, I'm gonna
be here for a while.

07:03.250 --> 07:07.254
I think this about as far as
Mama wanna go for a while.

07:11.120 --> 07:13.847
[WHISPERING] Point to point.

07:13.985 --> 07:16.781
Mother, why don't you just
let me help you with that?

07:16.919 --> 07:18.092
Well, who taught you?

07:19.922 --> 07:21.958
Well, then, that answers
that then, don't it?

07:24.271 --> 07:25.824
[DOOR OPENING]

07:25.962 --> 07:27.654
Huh.

07:27.792 --> 07:31.347
That'll be the number one prodigal
returning safe and sound.

07:32.003 --> 07:33.314
Hallelujah.

07:34.833 --> 07:37.802
I guess I will
go on to the bathroom

07:39.320 --> 07:40.805
before dinner.

07:42.323 --> 07:44.291
Everything's moving,

07:44.429 --> 07:45.948
and Mama grooving.

07:46.086 --> 07:47.467
MARCUS: In Jesus' name,
let the good children say...

07:48.053 --> 07:49.434
ALL: Amen!

07:49.572 --> 07:50.746
Amen!

07:52.126 --> 07:54.404
So,

07:54.543 --> 07:57.718
Janay's having a sleepover
tonight and she invited me.

07:57.856 --> 07:59.375
Is her parents
going to be there?

08:00.514 --> 08:01.895
Her mom will be.

08:02.033 --> 08:03.862
Not her father?

08:04.000 --> 08:07.072
I'm sure, Mama, if she knew who her
father was she would let you know.

08:07.210 --> 08:09.385
It's "Mother."

08:09.523 --> 08:11.456
I'm sure, Mother, if she knew...

08:11.594 --> 08:14.183
Girl, is the light bulb over
your head burnt out?

08:16.012 --> 08:17.186
Let me help you
with that, Mother.

08:17.324 --> 08:18.946
MAMA: I got it. Well, all right.

08:20.879 --> 08:21.915
You can go, baby girl.

08:22.053 --> 08:23.019
Thanks, Daddy.

08:23.157 --> 08:24.193
Mmm-hmm.

08:33.029 --> 08:35.549
I promise I'll clean up my room and
do my homework in the morning.

08:38.000 --> 08:40.208
Okay.

08:40.347 --> 08:42.936
Hey, Marg, I got to go into the
office tomorrow for a while.

08:43.073 --> 08:44.731
Here we go.

08:44.869 --> 08:46.456
I thought you said that you were

08:46.595 --> 08:49.114
done with Saturdays and
that that project was over.

08:49.252 --> 08:50.530
MARCUS: I guess
this is a new one.

08:51.427 --> 08:52.739
This is a new project.

08:54.844 --> 08:56.605
Well, this is the sacrifice
you gotta make.

08:58.054 --> 09:00.263
You want food on the table?

09:00.401 --> 09:02.093
It's either this or Sunday. No!

09:03.128 --> 09:04.164
No!

09:04.302 --> 09:05.683
I understand.

09:06.925 --> 09:08.617
Well, if, if I was gone...

09:08.755 --> 09:09.721
[CHOKING]

09:10.929 --> 09:12.068
MARGARET: Mother!

09:12.206 --> 09:13.863
LUCIA: Will water help?

09:14.001 --> 09:15.209
Come on. Lift 'em up!

09:15.347 --> 09:17.211
Woman, if you didn't
take such big bites...

09:17.349 --> 09:18.454
Marcus, not now!

09:18.592 --> 09:19.938
Don't disrespect me in my house.

09:20.870 --> 09:22.009
Lean back.

09:22.147 --> 09:23.424
Work is calling.

09:26.048 --> 09:28.602
LUCIA: Okay, gross. I'm going.

09:28.740 --> 09:29.914
I'm going to get dressed.

09:30.052 --> 09:31.122
Thank you, Jesus.

09:32.295 --> 09:34.435
I thought I was
gonna meet Jesus.

09:34.574 --> 09:36.817
[BREATHES RASPILY]

09:36.955 --> 09:39.305
But at least it was
nice to know it would

09:39.317 --> 09:41.511
have been over some
fine home cooking.

09:41.650 --> 09:43.168
[LAUGHING]

09:45.481 --> 09:46.965
Oh-oh.

09:49.830 --> 09:51.176
Ooh.

09:52.626 --> 09:54.179
[EXHALES]

09:54.317 --> 09:55.525
Saturday's all set, baby.

09:56.941 --> 09:58.494
Be available for you
all day Sunday.

09:58.632 --> 09:59.840
Not a problem.

10:02.843 --> 10:04.604
Mmm. This is
the best salad.

10:05.432 --> 10:07.779
<i>♪ I have hurt</i>

10:07.917 --> 10:09.332
<i>♪ God</i>

10:09.470 --> 10:14.096
<i>♪ I have sinned</i>

10:14.234 --> 10:20.136
<i>♪ I have idols
I have scars and addictions</i>

10:21.310 --> 10:25.107
<i>♪ But by your love, God</i>

10:25.245 --> 10:29.283
<i>♪ You called my name</i>

10:29.421 --> 10:32.977
<i>♪ And I am saved</i>

10:33.115 --> 10:37.326
<i>♪ I am saved ♪</i>

10:43.643 --> 10:44.885
That was good.

10:47.129 --> 10:48.371
It started good.

10:48.958 --> 10:49.890
That's all.

10:50.546 --> 10:52.030
Thanks.

10:54.343 --> 10:56.725
I was working on the
ending when I got home.

10:57.967 --> 10:59.900
I like your bridge, though.

11:00.038 --> 11:01.591
It's what's been missing.

11:04.560 --> 11:07.080
You're too quick to keep the G.

11:07.218 --> 11:08.909
It shouldn't resolve so easily.

11:09.047 --> 11:10.083
[CHUCKLES]

11:10.221 --> 11:12.257
That's what I was thinking, too.

11:12.395 --> 11:15.157
Maybe not the way
people think it should.

11:15.295 --> 11:18.229
I can go get
my guitar and show you.

11:22.474 --> 11:23.648
Yeah,

11:26.237 --> 11:27.376
you're probably right.

11:27.514 --> 11:29.171
I'm right a lot.

11:29.309 --> 11:30.655
Not that it matters.

11:31.691 --> 11:32.899
[DOOR OPENS]

11:39.940 --> 11:41.183
What's wrong?

11:43.219 --> 11:44.565
MARCUS: Levi.

11:46.257 --> 11:47.292
Levi Lewis.

11:48.190 --> 11:50.019
Get over here!

11:54.092 --> 11:55.715
[HORN HONKING]

11:59.235 --> 12:00.236
Bye, Daddy, see you tomorrow.

12:00.374 --> 12:01.617
Uh-huh.

12:06.864 --> 12:08.037
LUCIA: Hey, ya'll.

12:08.520 --> 12:09.867
Turn up.

12:10.005 --> 12:12.455
Hi, Ms. Thompson.
How you doin'?

12:12.593 --> 12:15.286
[ALL CHEERING]

12:26.124 --> 12:28.437
MR. NORDOFF: That was good,
guys. See you later.

12:29.369 --> 12:31.233
Brianna, you ready?

12:32.165 --> 12:33.200
No.

12:33.856 --> 12:35.030
Why not?

12:37.135 --> 12:38.619
Can we talk in private?

12:39.689 --> 12:40.967
Sure.

12:41.105 --> 12:42.796
Come in my office.

12:57.638 --> 12:58.916
Everything okay?

13:02.160 --> 13:04.335
Look, I'm trying here.

13:04.473 --> 13:06.026
I'm not trying to be
BFFs or anything.

13:06.993 --> 13:08.718
It's personal.

13:08.857 --> 13:10.341
You wouldn't want
to be involved.

13:10.479 --> 13:11.791
Rock the boat.

13:11.929 --> 13:13.240
Boat's already rocking.

13:14.586 --> 13:16.243
Is it the same thing?

13:17.797 --> 13:19.039
You know?

13:19.177 --> 13:20.489
I've always known.

13:20.627 --> 13:21.801
You haven't fixed it?

13:23.768 --> 13:25.459
Too many things to fix.

13:25.597 --> 13:26.667
Low priority.

13:26.806 --> 13:28.186
Look.

13:28.324 --> 13:29.705
We haven't been talking,

13:29.843 --> 13:31.534
but it's got to start somewhere.

13:31.672 --> 13:33.605
I could help you, you know.

13:36.608 --> 13:38.645
We could help each other.

13:38.783 --> 13:40.164
Then you won't feel indebted.

13:43.374 --> 13:44.547
Good job.

13:44.685 --> 13:45.721
Thanks Mr. N.Yeah.

13:47.067 --> 13:48.897
We'll talk again soon, Brianna.

13:49.035 --> 13:50.415
Don't forget what I said.

13:55.800 --> 13:58.044
You really would help me?

13:58.182 --> 13:59.252
I said I would.

13:59.390 --> 14:01.185
You said a lot of things.

14:01.323 --> 14:03.256
Double driven.
You know?

14:04.429 --> 14:05.775
I'm not hopeful.

14:05.914 --> 14:07.053
Hope is all we have right now.

14:07.881 --> 14:09.262
Like I said,

14:09.400 --> 14:11.678
I think this could be
the start of something

14:11.816 --> 14:13.783
new, a fresh beginning.

14:14.370 --> 14:15.406
For everyone.

14:15.544 --> 14:16.752
I don't know.

14:16.890 --> 14:18.581
I got a lot going on. Yeah, right.

14:19.341 --> 14:20.411
You don't know me!

14:20.549 --> 14:22.516
Enough to know you have time.

14:22.654 --> 14:24.070
It's been long enough.

14:26.520 --> 14:27.901
Meet me here.

14:29.075 --> 14:30.870
Safety zone!

14:38.429 --> 14:39.740
I guess we can try.

14:42.467 --> 14:43.537
Okay, then.

14:44.159 --> 14:45.505
Step one.

14:46.609 --> 14:47.748
Check.

15:04.869 --> 15:06.112
[CELL PHONE BEEPS]

15:10.116 --> 15:11.427
[CLEARS THROAT]

15:16.570 --> 15:18.331
MAMA: Lord have mercy.

15:18.469 --> 15:22.059
I am about to stick my
foot all up in this.

15:22.197 --> 15:23.232
Mmm-hmm.

15:23.370 --> 15:24.716
[CHUCKLES]

15:30.136 --> 15:32.448
I have to work again
tomorrow. Boy.

15:33.449 --> 15:36.038
Mmm-hmm. Mmm!

15:36.176 --> 15:40.318
Ain't nothing like the good cooking
of a woman who loves Jesus.

15:42.113 --> 15:45.599
We're studying the dynamic of
family in sociology, Mama.

15:45.737 --> 15:47.498
Oh, really, is that right?

15:47.636 --> 15:49.224
Well, tell me.

15:49.362 --> 15:52.399
What does the school book say
that the good book can't?

15:52.537 --> 15:55.540
Well, we're talking
about family and

15:55.678 --> 15:59.199
the connection of roles
and how the lack

15:59.337 --> 16:01.270
of socialization within a unit.

16:02.858 --> 16:04.825
American studies
show that American families

16:04.964 --> 16:06.793
are just not happening anymore.

16:06.931 --> 16:08.726
Any, more.

16:09.969 --> 16:11.453
Roll those eyes again.

16:12.247 --> 16:13.524
It's very interesting.

16:13.662 --> 16:15.284
Do you know that out of
eight of my homegirls,

16:15.422 --> 16:17.977
only two of them have parents
that are still together?

16:18.425 --> 16:20.462
Hmm.

16:20.600 --> 16:22.843
That's because they
don't value the home.

16:22.982 --> 16:27.158
Do not value the importance of
sitting down together each evening

16:29.471 --> 16:30.782
and reconnecting.

16:30.920 --> 16:32.129
Well, back in my day,

16:32.784 --> 16:34.545
it was a given.

16:34.683 --> 16:36.685
You'll get whooped silly
if you missed supper time.

16:36.823 --> 16:40.861
Oh, that's right! You would get whooped
for disrespecting the family that way.

16:44.106 --> 16:45.935
What do you know
about respect, Levi?

16:46.902 --> 16:49.525
Oh, he knows, son.
He knows.

16:51.182 --> 16:52.735
I'm asking Levi!

16:53.702 --> 16:54.910
Here.

16:55.048 --> 16:56.429
Here's your pills, Mama.

16:56.567 --> 16:58.362
Go on, pass those
to your grandma.

17:00.226 --> 17:02.711
Dressing it up don't make
it a thing you, know?

17:03.574 --> 17:05.438
Anyways, um,

17:05.576 --> 17:09.234
I asked my friends if they all sit
and have dinner with their families.

17:09.373 --> 17:11.789
And they had some
interesting stories.

17:11.926 --> 17:13.480
Mmm-hmm.

17:13.617 --> 17:16.242
You know, this gathering
is a bit archaic.

17:16.380 --> 17:19.969
You know, a TV dinner in front
of a box don't make a family.

17:20.108 --> 17:21.522
Mmm-mmm.

17:21.661 --> 17:23.318
Silent gatherings don't either.

17:31.498 --> 17:33.121
Are you okay, Levi?

17:33.259 --> 17:34.501
Yes, ma'am.
I'm fine.

17:36.745 --> 17:38.850
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

17:41.474 --> 17:43.441
Got anything else you
like to say there, Levi?

17:44.580 --> 17:46.168
LEVI: No, sir. Huh?

17:47.273 --> 17:49.137
No, sir. What's that?

17:49.275 --> 17:50.414
No, sir.

17:54.314 --> 17:56.144
[GLASS CLINKING]

17:57.835 --> 17:59.871
I'm proud to announce that

18:00.009 --> 18:04.600
this Saturday, I'm sorry, this Sunday,
I'll be serving for the pastor.

18:04.738 --> 18:07.983
Seem to me it ain't the
pastor who needs protecting.

18:08.121 --> 18:09.847
I think it's actually
a great thing.

18:11.918 --> 18:14.714
And I can assure you
that me and the family

18:14.852 --> 18:16.785
will make sure that
we're there on time

18:16.923 --> 18:18.821
ready to support you.

18:18.959 --> 18:20.513
It's the least we can do.

18:22.446 --> 18:24.310
Go on and take
your pills, Mother.

18:24.448 --> 18:26.001
Mama is fine.

18:30.247 --> 18:31.386
See?

18:33.077 --> 18:34.665
No, no need to fuss.

18:36.425 --> 18:37.495
Everything's perfect.

18:39.428 --> 18:42.949
<i>♪ Search me</i>

18:43.087 --> 18:46.125
<i>♪ Oh, God</i>

18:46.263 --> 18:49.128
<i>♪ Know my heart</i>

18:53.304 --> 18:56.445
<i>♪ Trust me ♪</i>

18:57.377 --> 18:58.827
I am trying!

18:58.965 --> 19:02.210
This is trying?
Get over yourself.

19:02.348 --> 19:05.696
See the chord in your
hand, an open chord.

19:05.834 --> 19:08.285
These are the
corresponding notes.

19:11.115 --> 19:12.151
This sucks.

19:13.290 --> 19:15.015
Yeah.

19:15.154 --> 19:17.535
But you gotta get this right or
Nordoff is going to kick you out,

19:17.673 --> 19:18.985
so it has to sink in.

