38:38.419 --> 38:40.697
Both ends starting
to reject it now.

38:40.835 --> 38:42.768
I should've stuck with
that fruit pizza.

38:42.906 --> 38:47.290
Come on, Levi, get me on inside before
I explode out here on this porch.

38:47.428 --> 38:49.706
Yes, ma'am. Lord have mercy.
I'm telling you.

38:50.431 --> 38:52.260
Child, back in 1960...

38:52.399 --> 38:54.987
No, no, that's all good.
No need to share.

38:55.125 --> 38:56.092
Oh.

38:56.230 --> 38:57.990
That's TMI, right?

38:58.128 --> 38:59.337
[ALL LAUGHING]

38:59.475 --> 39:02.340
Come on. You can bring
my walker in behind me.

39:02.478 --> 39:03.755
Yes, ma'am.Okay.

39:15.560 --> 39:18.217
There is a slight chill in the air
as you heard from Raindrop Bob

39:18.356 --> 39:20.012
in his report.

39:20.150 --> 39:21.186
So get ready, looks like
there is a storm coming.

39:22.670 --> 39:24.638
In other news, two youth
in North Carolina

39:24.776 --> 39:28.538
are brought to trial for pushing
a young girl down a storm drain.

39:28.676 --> 39:30.195
Authorities are calling it
a hate crime.

39:41.517 --> 39:43.035
[ENGINE REVVING]

39:44.174 --> 39:45.624
Jesus!

39:45.762 --> 39:48.213
Bri, whatever is said right
now, just stay out of it, okay?

39:57.705 --> 39:58.637
What the hell is going on here?

39:58.775 --> 40:00.087
Dad! Get in the car.

40:00.225 --> 40:01.916
No, Dad. Get in the car!

40:02.054 --> 40:03.677
Dad, wait!

40:03.815 --> 40:05.472
So this is what got
your mother upset?

40:05.610 --> 40:07.819
I don't know is it? What are
you doing on a Saturday night?

40:14.101 --> 40:15.240
Boy.

40:15.965 --> 40:16.931
This ain't over.

40:17.622 --> 40:18.761
This part is.

40:32.084 --> 40:33.120
Are you okay?

40:34.397 --> 40:36.157
Yeah. I'm fine.

40:36.295 --> 40:37.987
Had to happen eventually.

40:38.125 --> 40:39.471
I'm so sorry, Levi.

40:39.609 --> 40:41.093
It's all good.

40:41.231 --> 40:43.130
No, it's not.
There's no excuse for that.

40:47.445 --> 40:48.515
Not that.

40:50.102 --> 40:51.621
But the rest.

40:54.141 --> 40:55.591
Just feels good to be free.

40:58.870 --> 41:02.114
Enough to write a song about it.

41:02.252 --> 41:03.391
Let's do it.

41:03.530 --> 41:04.876
Yeah.

41:05.014 --> 41:06.498
[CHUCKLES]

41:09.467 --> 41:10.640
Hey, Dad!

41:10.778 --> 41:12.159
Hey, Bri.

41:12.297 --> 41:14.230
Wow, you sound happy.

41:14.368 --> 41:17.509
You know what? I think I am.
Nice change, huh?

41:17.647 --> 41:20.650
Very nice. Say, can you
help me with this?

41:22.065 --> 41:23.204
Yeah.

41:24.620 --> 41:25.655
Thanks.

41:26.138 --> 41:27.519
Wonder Girl.

41:27.657 --> 41:28.762
Woman.

41:29.107 --> 41:30.211
Huh?

41:30.349 --> 41:31.972
Wonder Woman, Dad.

41:32.110 --> 41:33.525
Not 14 anymore.

41:34.595 --> 41:35.838
Oh, yeah?

41:38.668 --> 41:40.532
Uh, we're good
on milk and stuff.

41:40.670 --> 41:42.085
I went to the store and...

41:42.223 --> 41:44.363
Sometimes I just wish
she were here, you know?

41:44.502 --> 41:45.986
She could talk to you
about things I...

41:46.124 --> 41:48.367
I don't know how
to talk to you about.

41:52.682 --> 41:53.925
She sucked at it anyway.

41:55.236 --> 41:56.686
You're doing great.

41:58.999 --> 42:00.518
In fact, uh,

42:01.208 --> 42:03.210
you're doing so great

42:03.348 --> 42:05.212
I want to talk to you
about something.

42:06.524 --> 42:07.973
Oh, yeah?

42:08.111 --> 42:10.251
Well, I don't know about that,
but what's up?

42:10.389 --> 42:11.529
You know I'm here for you.

42:11.667 --> 42:12.944
And I'm here for you.

42:15.463 --> 42:19.088
How would you feel about
going to a counselor?

42:19.226 --> 42:20.676
Huh?

42:21.366 --> 42:22.540
Uh...

42:23.679 --> 42:24.645
Well, uh...

42:27.441 --> 42:29.270
Look, I mean, I know
they're nice, but you know,

42:29.408 --> 42:32.342
I'm already taking
too many pills and

42:32.480 --> 42:34.621
I'm shaky, I need to
focus at work.

42:34.759 --> 42:38.728
I was thinking maybe
not that kind of counselor.

42:38.866 --> 42:41.041
Just someone you can
talk to one on one

42:41.179 --> 42:43.181
without having to be
prescribed something.

42:44.734 --> 42:46.805
[SIGHS]

42:46.943 --> 42:48.635
I was talking to Levi and...

42:48.773 --> 42:50.740
You mean you were
talking to Levi?

42:50.878 --> 42:52.466
When? No, Dad, it's okay.

42:52.604 --> 42:54.295
He talked to me first.

42:54.433 --> 42:57.505
We sort of came to
an understanding.

42:57.644 --> 43:00.163
We've even been
writing music together.

43:01.337 --> 43:03.132
And he's been teaching me
to read music.

43:05.134 --> 43:06.687
It's pretty cool.

43:06.825 --> 43:08.516
To have someone to talk to.

43:12.382 --> 43:13.729
Oh.

43:14.592 --> 43:16.663
Anyway,

43:16.801 --> 43:19.976
he told me about
this gal at his church.

43:20.114 --> 43:23.152
She's a pastor but also
a licensed counselor.

43:25.050 --> 43:28.157
He said she helped
him through a lot.

43:28.295 --> 43:31.609
And I met with her too,
and she's pretty cool.

43:31.747 --> 43:33.818
Did you tell her about me?
About what happened?

43:35.578 --> 43:36.786
Yes.

43:37.822 --> 43:39.133
Oh.

43:39.271 --> 43:40.618
It's not her place to judge.

43:43.137 --> 43:45.001
It would really
help you, you know?

43:45.933 --> 43:48.142
Talk to someone.

43:48.280 --> 43:49.696
Don't I have to go
to church there?

43:49.834 --> 43:52.284
No. It's totally for
anyone who needs help.

43:55.425 --> 43:56.979
Ah.

43:57.117 --> 43:58.463
Three or four on that day.

43:59.188 --> 44:00.499
Three, Dad.

44:00.638 --> 44:01.569
Oh, yeah.

44:01.708 --> 44:04.055
Anyway, um,

44:04.193 --> 44:07.955
I spoke with her and she's totally
open to meeting with you.

44:09.474 --> 44:11.510
I even made you an appointment.

44:12.891 --> 44:15.411
I can cancel it
at any time or you can,

44:15.549 --> 44:17.344
but I hope,

44:18.241 --> 44:20.209
I pray you'll consider it.

44:23.212 --> 44:24.834
I haven't been to church
in a long time, Bri.

44:26.318 --> 44:27.768
Doesn't mean you don't believe.

44:29.943 --> 44:31.047
[CHUCKLES]

44:31.185 --> 44:33.187
You have her wit.
I missed that.

44:35.465 --> 44:37.951
Please, Dad, talk to someone.

44:40.022 --> 44:42.093
Please, Dad.

44:42.231 --> 44:43.784
It'll help. I'm tired, Bri.

44:44.474 --> 44:45.683
Okay, um...

44:45.821 --> 44:48.306
I will seriously think about it.

44:49.721 --> 44:51.723
Thanks for thinking of me.

44:51.861 --> 44:53.380
I'm always thinking of you, Dad.

44:55.037 --> 44:56.279
Singing about me?

44:58.040 --> 45:01.388
Everything seems to come up
in a song one way or another.

45:19.924 --> 45:21.753
[DOORBELL RINGS]

45:21.891 --> 45:23.030
I'll get it, Mom.

45:26.206 --> 45:28.726
Do we have to wait for
Daddy or can we go ahead?

45:32.246 --> 45:33.385
Ladies.

45:34.421 --> 45:35.940
I think you know this stranger.

45:37.873 --> 45:39.771
Honey.

45:39.909 --> 45:43.430
Aren't you gonna welcome baby B into
your house like you would any guest?

45:43.568 --> 45:46.433
It took a lot for her to trust
to come through this door.

45:50.506 --> 45:51.610
Brianna,

45:56.236 --> 45:58.272
let me go and, uh,

45:58.410 --> 45:59.964
set another place
setting for you.

46:00.102 --> 46:01.759
Mother.

46:01.897 --> 46:03.415
She can sit next to me.

46:07.143 --> 46:08.593
Come here, Bri.

46:08.731 --> 46:10.008
Follow me.

46:20.950 --> 46:22.331
It's not you, B.

46:22.469 --> 46:24.264
She just waiting on Daddy
to show up and pray.

46:24.747 --> 46:26.369
Mmm-hmm.

46:26.507 --> 46:31.547
Every night we wait seven minutes or
at least until the food gets cold

46:31.685 --> 46:33.687
in hopes that he
is going to show up.

46:35.447 --> 46:37.760
Every night, every day.

46:37.898 --> 46:39.935
Tick. Tock.Lucia.

46:40.073 --> 46:41.591
The truth hurts, Mother.

46:41.729 --> 46:43.524
Levi.

46:44.180 --> 46:45.423
Go ahead.

46:47.356 --> 46:48.495
LEVI: Father God,

46:49.599 --> 46:51.636
thank you for your grace,

46:51.774 --> 46:53.845
your mercy and your hope.

46:55.019 --> 46:56.952
Thank you for our
guest today, Lord.

46:58.229 --> 47:00.576
Bless the food to
nourish our bodies.

47:01.473 --> 47:02.750
In Jesus' name...

47:03.337 --> 47:05.167
ALL: Amen.

47:06.754 --> 47:10.206
Mama. I'm a growing woman.Mmm-hmm.

47:10.344 --> 47:13.900
You practicing at being grown. Now,
I don't know about the rest of it.

47:14.038 --> 47:15.694
Ha, ha. Mama got jokes.

47:15.833 --> 47:16.868
[LAUGHING]

47:18.766 --> 47:22.736
Anyway, what did you learn
in school today, child?

47:22.874 --> 47:26.395
That Suzanna Moore is a liar
and a boyfriend stealer.

47:26.533 --> 47:29.398
Can't steal what ain't
available to you, honey.

47:29.536 --> 47:31.469
I didn't know.
Nobody told me.

47:31.607 --> 47:33.333
Everybody knows that, Lucia.

47:33.471 --> 47:36.370
Doesn't matter. She had a nice
little surprise in her locker today.

47:36.508 --> 47:39.270
Oh, my.
LUCIA: Mmm-hmm.

47:39.408 --> 47:41.720
Yeah, she was crying
and fussing on.

47:41.859 --> 47:44.689
Kicking and screaming.
They had to escort her out.

47:44.827 --> 47:46.587
MAMA: Well, serves her right.

47:46.725 --> 47:48.072
If she not guilty.

47:48.210 --> 47:49.556
Oh, she's guilty.

47:50.177 --> 47:51.385
Right, Bri?

47:52.352 --> 47:54.526
Uh, I mean,

47:54.664 --> 47:57.667
kind of obvious,
but I'm not sure.

47:57.805 --> 47:59.635
What are you talking about?

47:59.773 --> 48:01.602
She made out with half
the football team.

48:01.740 --> 48:03.881
Ooh, child.

48:05.399 --> 48:06.607
Just half.

48:06.745 --> 48:08.540
The other half is
the basketball team.

48:08.678 --> 48:11.923
MAMA: Oh, no, child.

48:14.339 --> 48:20.345
Now that's what you call, back in
my day, a lady of many colors.

48:20.483 --> 48:22.106
[ALL LAUGHING]

48:22.244 --> 48:24.487
Is that why they called you
colorful back in the day, Mama?

48:24.625 --> 48:28.871
MAMA: Oh, you stop that, girl.
Hush now.

48:29.009 --> 48:31.736
Don't be spreading
that rumor around.

48:31.874 --> 48:34.152
Back in my day, now, I was...

48:34.290 --> 48:36.741
Bootylicious!
LUCIA: Bootylicious!

48:44.369 --> 48:47.717
What the hell is
going on in here?

48:47.855 --> 48:48.891
Marcus.

48:49.029 --> 48:50.272
Shut up, Margaret.

48:50.410 --> 48:52.136
Dad. You shut up, too.

48:53.482 --> 48:55.933
Someone tell me why
she at my dinner table.

48:56.071 --> 48:58.245
Marcus. I said shut it up.

48:58.383 --> 48:59.867
LEVI: Dad, stop.

49:00.006 --> 49:03.526
Someone better tell me
why she's at my dinner table.

49:03.664 --> 49:05.632
Maybe I should go. No!

49:06.944 --> 49:08.980
You're not going anywhere.

49:09.118 --> 49:11.017
It's always like you, Levi.

49:13.019 --> 49:15.193
Getting in business that
don't belong to you.

49:19.301 --> 49:20.819
Stirring things up.

49:21.682 --> 49:23.339
This is my house.

49:24.202 --> 49:25.824
And this is my table.

49:28.620 --> 49:30.864
[MARGARET CHUCKLING]

49:31.002 --> 49:32.659
Woman? Mama?

49:41.599 --> 49:42.703
It's mother.

49:46.155 --> 49:47.329
Mother.

49:49.572 --> 49:50.642
Mother.

49:52.334 --> 49:53.473
Mother!

49:55.785 --> 49:57.649
Mo-ther.

50:03.966 --> 50:05.588
It's your table?

50:05.726 --> 50:07.487
Hmm? It's your table?

50:11.249 --> 50:12.733
Look at you.

50:13.562 --> 50:15.150
You disgust me.

50:16.703 --> 50:18.601
I'll do what I have to do.

50:19.568 --> 50:21.259
But no more.

50:24.435 --> 50:27.093
No more!

50:27.231 --> 50:30.544
No more dealing with
this false pretending!

50:32.408 --> 50:34.100
False pretending.

50:35.170 --> 50:36.585
Margaret.

50:36.723 --> 50:39.657
Don't you freaking even fix
your mouth to Margaret me.

50:41.003 --> 50:43.557
You dirty, slimy dog.

50:44.662 --> 50:46.733
[CRYING]

50:48.493 --> 50:50.185
I had enough!

50:53.188 --> 50:54.948
I gotta,

50:55.086 --> 50:59.090
I gotta, I gotta,
I gotta stand here

51:01.092 --> 51:05.924
and watch her sit in
my dead son's chair.

51:13.587 --> 51:18.075
He ain't sitting here
smiling. She is!

51:19.214 --> 51:20.767
Get up!

51:24.943 --> 51:26.773
And you.

51:26.911 --> 51:31.502
Just say whatever you want out of
your mouth like it doesn't affect me.

51:33.987 --> 51:35.437
And then you.

51:36.576 --> 51:38.440
I'm talking to you, Levi.

51:38.578 --> 51:40.442
Yeah, you're not going
to get off easy either.

51:41.719 --> 51:43.238
Golden boy.

51:44.273 --> 51:46.931
I got to watch you giggle it up.

51:47.069 --> 51:48.312
Like it's a joke.

51:49.140 --> 51:50.590
And bringing her here.

51:55.629 --> 51:59.944
And Mama, you go ahead and
you look off into the sunset.

52:00.082 --> 52:05.191
The first time in how many years
that your mouth is finally quiet?

52:05.329 --> 52:09.747
But you know what? Most
of all I'm tired of you.

52:10.713 --> 52:14.131
You disgust me in so many ways.

52:15.132 --> 52:16.547
You know why?

52:16.685 --> 52:18.376
'Cause you left me here

52:18.963 --> 52:20.620
to grieve

52:21.517 --> 52:23.001
the death

52:23.692 --> 52:25.142
of my son

52:26.350 --> 52:28.352
all by myself,

52:28.490 --> 52:33.495
while you went out there and
entertained every woman you could.

52:34.151 --> 52:36.083
You're disgusting.

52:38.638 --> 52:40.226
You're not a man!

52:44.368 --> 52:47.060
I can't take it anymore.

52:47.198 --> 52:51.996
Oh, God. Oh, God. Mama, I'm sorry.
I'm so sorry.

52:52.928 --> 52:54.757
I didn't mean it.

52:54.895 --> 52:57.898
I didn't mean it.
I'm sorry. I love you.

52:58.036 --> 52:59.900
I love you, Mommy.

53:00.038 --> 53:02.731
LUCIA: I'm so sorry.
MARGARET: Oh God, please.

53:02.869 --> 53:04.629
I just want my baby back.

53:07.494 --> 53:08.633
I'm tired.

53:14.708 --> 53:16.054
I'm tired.

53:16.193 --> 53:17.401
[THUDS]

53:17.539 --> 53:21.094
Who the hell do you
think you are

53:21.232 --> 53:23.579
bringing her up
in here like that?

53:26.444 --> 53:28.412
Whatever it is

53:28.550 --> 53:31.208
it's ten times more than
the man you'll ever be.

53:31.346 --> 53:32.726
Oh, yeah?

53:32.864 --> 53:34.487
Well, I'm going to get her
out of here right now!

53:34.625 --> 53:37.110
Stop! Somebody stop them.

53:37.248 --> 53:39.043
Somebody stop them.

53:39.699 --> 53:41.390
Please.

53:41.908 --> 53:43.220
BRI: Dad!

53:43.358 --> 53:44.635
Don't you come back
in here again.

53:44.773 --> 53:45.912
Don't you come back.
Get your hands off of her.

53:47.396 --> 53:48.915
Come back here.
Huh? Huh?

53:49.053 --> 53:50.537
[GRUNTS]

53:50.675 --> 53:53.022
Go! Get out of here.

53:53.160 --> 53:54.265
LEVI: Are you okay? Dad!

53:54.403 --> 53:56.094
No, stay back.

54:00.098 --> 54:01.203
Daddy!

54:02.204 --> 54:04.206
BRI: No, stop!

54:04.344 --> 54:05.690
You want some of me, Steve?

54:05.828 --> 54:06.898
Huh?

54:07.036 --> 54:08.417
Stop!

54:08.555 --> 54:10.454
[GRUNTING]

54:12.007 --> 54:13.457
You're killing him!

54:14.216 --> 54:15.182
No!

54:15.321 --> 54:16.701
Stop! Please!

54:16.839 --> 54:18.324
Let him go. You want to know what's
wrong with me?

54:18.462 --> 54:20.464
You got the nerve to ask
what's wrong with me?

54:20.602 --> 54:22.604
You know darn well what's
wrong with me.

54:22.742 --> 54:24.330
You killed my boy.

54:24.468 --> 54:26.849
LUCIA: Let him go! You killed the
one that carried this family.

54:26.987 --> 54:28.920
You killed the one
that was good.

54:30.508 --> 54:32.027
No!

54:32.165 --> 54:35.341
Then you sitting there like you
all good and you're sorry.

54:35.479 --> 54:36.928
But sorry doesn't
bring him back!

54:38.171 --> 54:40.622
I'm going to break
your neck, Steve!

54:44.591 --> 54:46.800
[GRUNTING]

54:49.803 --> 54:52.254
LEVI: Let him, let him go.
You're killing him!

54:57.811 --> 54:59.675
You want to try
your father, huh?

54:59.813 --> 55:01.436
Stop! You're a big man now?

55:02.506 --> 55:04.335
[COUGHING]

55:04.473 --> 55:06.130
You want to come at
your father like that?

55:06.268 --> 55:07.304
Huh?

55:08.822 --> 55:09.927
Daddy!

55:10.065 --> 55:11.653
I never did like you.

55:11.791 --> 55:12.930
LUCIA: Daddy, stop.

55:14.276 --> 55:15.346
Marcus!

55:17.279 --> 55:18.315
No, Dad.

55:18.453 --> 55:19.661
I'm going to take your head off!

55:21.145 --> 55:22.422
Dad, stop!

55:22.560 --> 55:24.838
You need to get
control of yourself.

55:25.770 --> 55:26.978
Stop.

55:29.602 --> 55:32.536
I wish it was you that day
that got hit with that car.

55:32.674 --> 55:34.261
Oh, my God. You should
have been the one.

55:38.369 --> 55:39.508
I wish

55:41.027 --> 55:42.511
you were dead!

55:42.649 --> 55:43.995
MARGARET: Marcus!

55:46.135 --> 55:47.413
No, no!

55:52.901 --> 55:55.248
MARGARET: No! No!

55:56.007 --> 55:57.802
No!

55:57.940 --> 55:59.494
Oh my God. Levi.

55:59.632 --> 56:00.874
MARGARET: Levi!

56:01.012 --> 56:03.808
Daddy why?
Oh, my God.

56:05.741 --> 56:09.987
Mama, what did I do?
What did I do, Mama?

56:13.646 --> 56:15.406
[LAUGHING]

56:15.544 --> 56:18.789
Well, Mother, when you done cutting
up out here with the youngins,

56:18.927 --> 56:20.929
come on in, 'cause
dinner's almost ready.

56:21.067 --> 56:22.033
All righty.

56:22.171 --> 56:23.483
All right.

56:23.621 --> 56:27.073
And, Bri, of course you
know you're welcome to stay.

56:27.211 --> 56:29.455
Yeah, baby.Thanks.

56:29.593 --> 56:30.870
Now, where was I?

56:32.734 --> 56:35.461
Oh, yeah, skating. That's
easy, even a girl can do it.

56:35.599 --> 56:37.980
Hey! Bri, I guess I'll show...

56:38.602 --> 56:39.913
Uh-oh.

56:40.431 --> 56:41.915
Uh-oh.

56:42.502 --> 56:44.124
That girl

56:44.262 --> 56:47.576
shouldn't be on that board though,
should she? She gone kill herself.

56:47.714 --> 56:49.060
She can handle her own, Mama.

56:50.579 --> 56:51.925
All righty.

56:52.857 --> 56:54.307
Mmm-hmm.

56:54.445 --> 56:56.689
Look, I can't take this anymore.

56:56.827 --> 57:00.762
You can't take it? Where are you going?
You going to see her?

57:00.900 --> 57:04.938
I can't take you anymore, Sara.
Now just stop it and let me go.

57:05.076 --> 57:06.284
Daddy, where you going?

57:06.423 --> 57:07.665
I gotta get away for a while,
